      "title": "Minimum Bracket Reversals",
      "topics": [],
      "fastest": true,
      "reverse": true,
      "shortest": false,
      "solution": "#include <stdio.h>\n#include <string.h>\n\nint main() {\n    char s[100005];\n    scanf(\"%s\", s);\n\n    int n = strlen(s);\n    if (n % 2 != 0) {\n        printf(\"-1\\n\");\n        return 0;\n    }\n\n    int open = 0, close = 0;\n\n    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {\n        if (s[i] == '{') {\n            open++;\n        } else {\n            if (open > 0)\n                open--;\n            else\n                close++;\n        }\n    }\n\n    int result = (open + 1) / 2 + (close + 1) / 2;\n    printf(\"%d\\n\", result);\n\n    return 0;\n}",
      "statement": "Given a string consisting only of curly brackets { and }, determine the minimum number of bracket reversals required to make the string balanced.\nA reversal changes { to } or } to {.\nIf it is impossible to balance the string, output -1.",
